// Ensure we are allowed to use this URL by config
' is invalid, ssh URLs should have a port number after ":".'
'Use ssh://git@example.com:22/path or just git@example.com:path if you do not want to provide a password or custom port.'
// capture username/password from URL if there is one and we have no auth configured yet
'Config value "github-protocols" must be an array, got '
// failed to checkout, first check git accessibility
// if we have a private github url and the ssh protocol is disabled then we skip it and directly fallback to https
// private github repository without ssh key access, try https with auth
'Cloning failed using an ssh key for authentication, enter your GitHub credentials to access private repos'
'Enter your Bitbucket credentials to access private repos'
//We're authenticating with a locally stored consumer.
//We already have an access_token from a previous request.
' No bitbucket authentication configured. Falling back to ssh.'
'Cloning failed, enter your GitLab credentials to access private repos'
// private non-github/gitlab/bitbucket repo that failed to authenticate
// update the repo if it is a valid git repository
'git remote set-url origin -- %s && git remote update --prune origin && git remote set-url origin -- %s && git gc --auto'
// clean up directory and do a fresh clone into it
'git remote set-url origin -- %s && git remote show origin && git remote set-url origin -- %s'
'<error>Failed to fetch root identifier from remote: '
// added in git 1.7.1, prevents prompting the user for username/password
// clean up rogue git env vars in case this is running in a git hook
// clean up env for OSX, see https://github.com/composer/composer/issues/2146#issuecomment-35478940
// git might delete a directory when it fails and php will not know
', git was not found, check that it is installed and in your PATH env.'
* @return string|null The git version number, if present.
